<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Duties:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> To establish and word topics to be voted on as set forth by the citizens of Brell through the medium of the BSnet boards; most specifically but not limited to, Raid Discussions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Practice:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> To meet once per week (in chat) to discuss issues that have been brought up or have been proposed by the citizens of Brell through the BSnet boards. To word and set forth the public voting of a topic, when consensus has been reached. To tally the votes and coordinate with the BSnet board moderators in the case of an issue addendum or addition. To maintain an open dialogue through the use of a web board for these purposes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Size:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 13 people.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Restrictions and Conditions:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The Vote Topic Group (VTG) will meet once per week at a predetermined time to discuss and possibly facilitate a public vote on an agreed upon topic. A member of the Vote Topic Group may not miss more then 1 meeting per month, or he/she will need to be replaced by a new member (taken from an alternate list of runner ups from the most recent VTG member vote).<br>
<br>
The VTG needs to have a 2/3s vote total to pass a topic for a public vote (in other words, this needs to be nearly unanimous to start a public vote).<br>
<br>
The VTG membership will be revoted (by the Brell public through the BSnet board) on once every three months. Current VTG members can be revoted in.<br>
<br>
The VTG cannot set or change the raid &quot;rules&quot; without a majority public vote from the citizens of Brell. A public vote must consist of at least 250 votes to be considered an &quot;official&quot; vote. <br>
<br>
The VTG has no opinion or desires other then to rate and vote upon whether a given topic is ready for a public vote.<br>
<br>
VTG voting upon the issuance of a topic will be made at the weekly meeting and must be 2/3's (or at least 9 votes of &quot;yes&quot;). Public voting will last one calendar week and tallied at the end of that week with the public vote being posted for all to see. Only one topic at any given time can be up for a public vote (this is so as not to confuse people with multiple topic voting).<br>
<br>
The VTG is NOT to be considered anything but an organizational body. It has no power or enforcement capabilities over the standard policies of Brell nor over any citizen of Brell. All policies are and have been set by the general consensus of the Brell public.<br>
<br>
The VTG may not have more then 2 members within the same guild. If at any time the VTG has more then 2 persons of the same guild (due to guild merger, or invite), the last person to have joined said guild (if applicable) will be asked to leave the VTG and the last runner up will replace said person.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Determining the VTG Membership:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A nomination thread will be set, where every unique person will nominate 5 individuals for the VTG. From this list, the most tallied top 26 names will be tallied and put forth for a vote. At this time, any of the 26 of this list should let be known whether he/she would like to serve as a VTG member or withdraw his/her name. Each of these 26 people will need to write a short biography of him/herself of their EQ career on Brell (time played, guilds joined, classes played, levels achieved, etc...) Each unique person will vote on 13 names of the 26 name roster. People who are on the final 26 person list, cannot vote for themselves. If the voted process produces a number of members of a particular guild that is more then 2, the next person with the most popular amount of votes who is not in that guild will replace that person. This form of voting will take place every 3 months starting from the conclusion of the first vote and in the same format.<br>
<br>
This is more or less the complete version of what I've been thinking about. Please feel free to add anything you think is missing and comment on whether you think this is a good idea for Brell or whether another system for developing and organizing the voting procedure is better or even needed. <p><FONT face="arial" size="-1"><B>Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)
