<br>
However I disagree with you on the voting blocks. First off, I would hope people would be intelligent enough to realize this is more of a job then any kind of glamour spot. It won't GAIN you anything by doing it, other than to help your fellow Brellian. Also, with the diversity we have on Brell, I think we can field a pretty good list of names.<br>
<br>
I don't think choosing the highest end members of the top 4 guilds is particularly healthy either. You do need some diversity among the VTG if for nothing else, perspective. Ever ask Nillon how he would do this raid or that? He only knows from the SR way. Put him with 40 sign ups, and he'd be lost. Sort of along those lines (not to pick on Nillon specifically).<br>
<br>
Saphdia: I don't think 2 people from the same guild would be influencial on the VTG in a one sided way. I specifcally minimized it to two people for this reason: you can vote for the person you think is best qualified (and alot of people know their own guildmates better then non-guildies) while at the same time not allow one guild to monopolize the VTG. I don't want to specifically deny a great candidate a spot because another great candidate happens to be from the same guild either. I thought it a good compromise.<br>
<br>
Nillon: I would think one of the ballots of voting on the VTG would be &quot;I don't support the VTG&quot;. Enough people vote like that and we don't use the VTG idea. Fair enough? <p><FONT face="arial" size="-1"><B>Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)
<BR><A HREF="http://www.krunch.net/spiritslammer">Clan Spiritslammer</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Lich</span><br>  Posts: 887<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/8/01 6:30:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vote Topic Group (revised)</span><hr size=1> I really don't see what the VTG has to discuss that we don't discuss on these boards.  It's pretty obvious when there is an issue.  I see no reason why only 13 people should discuss the issues. <p><br><font face="Arial" size="-2">Vumil Darksoul<br>
<a href=http://sr.amiga.tm>Silent Redemption</a><br>
<a href=http://www.brellserilis.net>Brell Serilis</a> Admin<br>
ICQ #: 33693268
</font>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Norrath's Finest Taxi Service</span><br>  Posts: 946<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/8/01 7:24:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vote Topic Group (revised)</span><hr size=1> Kruunch:<br>
<br>
Ideas like this inevitably degenerate into a popularity contest.  I know what you're trying to do; essentially, you're trying to &quot;get things done.&quot;  I have no problem with this.  I don't even necessarily think its a bad idea; however, I don't think its a good idea either.<br>
<br>
What it boils down to is I don't like the idea of someone (even the willing) having to schedule a weekly meeting for games.  Furthermore, anyone who's ever been on a committee of the size you suggest can tell you that 13 people is entirely too many.  You'll end up spending 3 hours trying to hammer out consensus on an issue because there's a subtlety of the wording that 7 like and 6 don't.  I know all about this Kruunch.  We did it at work.  It was called &quot;Quality Through Partnership&quot; and it only had six people on the committee...what it should have been called was &quot;Stalemate Through Nitpicky Bullshit.&quot;<br>
<br>
If you really want something like this to work, reduce that number from 13 to 3....maybe 5 at the most.  And select ONLY reasonable people who see the value of compromise and being rational.  If you choose only individuals who are interested in their &quot;phat l3wts&quot; you're going to get nowhere.<br>
<br>
Finally, keep in mind that the most reasonable of people may not be interested in spending their gaming time offline in a chat room for the betterment of the server.  Those individuals might be more interested in actually playing the game than doing something like this.  A proposal like this, as solid as it appears on the surface, can easily backfire and turn into an abortion of its intent. <p><BR>
