</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/8/01 8:46:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vote Topic Group (revised)</span><hr size=1> I don't like 66% majority. You have NO idea how difficult that is to get. It (obviously) means that on every proposal one side's vote is worth two of the other.  Not to mention, it's almost impossible to get anything done.<br>
<br>
66% more than anything else will doom voting to failure. If you must set some kind of &quot;majority&quot; it should be the simple majority. More than half, period.<br>
<br>
As Krunnch stated, Zest, your idea that this will become a popularity test is .. perhaps a bit premature. I'd like to first try it and see if that happened.<br>
<br>
Not to point any fingers, but right now, Brell HAS a VTG, and you, Vumil, Goat and perhaps Adune are it.<br>
<br>
Sindarre, <br>
I don't think it's fair to pick ANY five guilds to represent the server, regardless of how much those guilds think they're capable of doing it. By narrowing it down to any five, again, you will have the masses thinking this is some elitist plot, and we're trying to avoid that. Regardless of how thoughtful, and selfless those guilds and/or people are or willing to be, human nature will dictate that people will become dissatisfied.<br>
<br>
Saph,<br>
<br>
1 or 2 reps from each guild...again, it's not that big of an issue to me, and I agree with Kruunch that we'd not want to eliminate a good person b/c another great person is from that same guild. However, in some regards, one person is a good idea...there are enough great people on the server that I think one rep from a guild will serve and allow more voices to be heard.  So, /shrug <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  either way works for me...<br>
