</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukruuunch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kruuunch</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 1394<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/9/01 6:46:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.krunch.net/kruunch-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vote Topic Group (revised)</span><hr size=1> Zesty: I'm well aware of group dynamics, especially in a debate type forum. If you recall, that's why I said the people we would want up on the VTG to be reasonable people who could compromise.<br>
<br>
Sindarre: I would hope we would have people in the VTG that wouldn't think about a voting block, much less actively set one up. But the pettiness of people never ceases to amaze me.<br>
<br>
Yes the VTG could get very ponderous, I agree. It's all in the execution. Yes it would be work. I've stated that and I'll reiterate that. It's more work then I currently would want to pursue to be honest (the main reason I would not want a spot on the VTG).<br>
